      "date": "2013-01-29 23:32:03.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6: (4 inline comments)\n\nI like this, not only does it honor the on disk format but I think it's much clearer this way.  Regarding compatibility I'm glad we're catching this before 2.4 there can't be many Lustre ZFS filesystems out there yet which is good.  We could try and manually remove the . and .. entries from our existing file systems but I doubt we'll bother.",
