        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-31 04:07:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7:\n\nAt some point, when we want to remove this workaround, either we can do so after the Sequoia filesystem has been reformatted or if we are confident that all such entries have been removed.\n\nOne way to ensure this would be to have it print out a warning message that a  duplicate \"..\" entry existed and then ask the administrator to rename such directories wants to correct the problem.  Then, running find over the filesystem would report all such errors and you could be cleaned up in one pass.\n\nSince the overhead of always filtering out the \".\" and \"..\" entries for each readdir() is non-zero, we might want to actively pursue this option for Sequoia, and remove the workaround for 2.5?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
